[4] Cholera - Congo DR (North Kivu)
Date: Tue 18 Nov 2008
Source: Easy Bourse [edited]
<http://www.easybourse.com/bourse-actualite/marches/unicef-warns-of-growing-cholera-risk-in-congo-564040>


Cholera is spreading quickly in eastern Congo where rebels are
fighting government troops, the UN Children's Fund (UNICEF) warned
Tuesday [18 Nov 2008]. Veronique Taveau, a UNICEF spokeswoman, told
journalists that 127 fresh cases had just been discovered in the
village of Ishasha, north of Goma and near the Ugandan border.

She said aid agencies couldn't get to many areas because of the
fighting. "There are numerous places we can't reach, which definitely
makes us fear a sizable rise in the number of cases," she said. "It
is vital that humanitarian access is allowed."

The cases "seem to have spread very quickly due to a lack of hygiene
and water," she said.

The WHO (World health Organisation) warned last week [week of 10 Nov
2008] that cholera poses a "serious risk" in the region where around
1000 cases have been reported since October 2008. Fighting between
Congolese government troops and followers of renegade Tutsi general
Laurent Nkunda has killed at least 100 civilians and displaced more
than 250 000, the UN and humanitarian groups have said.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[A map of eastern Congo DR can be found at
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/eastdrc.pdf>.
As reported below, the disease is now spreading across the border
into western Uganda. - Mod.LL]

