[5] Cholera - Uganda (Kanungu) ex Congo DR
Date: Mon 17 Nov 2008
Source: The New Vision (Uganda) [edited]
<http://www.newvision.co.ug/D/8/18/659961>


At least one person has been reported dead of suspected cholera among
the Congolese refugees who entered Uganda. They are fleeing the
fighting in the DR Congo. Kanungu district director of health
services Dr Stephen Ssebude said cholera and dysentery have been
reported in Congo about 10 km (6.2 mi) from the Uganda-Congo border
where a 14-year-old child was reported dead.

An official with the Red Cross, Charles Cadet, said about 1200
people, who intended to cross to Uganda have been denied entry by the
army on the Congo side. They were reportedly living in unhygienic
conditions, which makes the disease spread quickly. However, they
entered Uganda after the soldiers who were preventing them from
entering the country fled to an unknown place on Wednesday [12 Nov 2008].

Cadet also said the army on the Congo side of the boarder, have on
several occasions tried to forcefully arrest people who have crossed to Uganda.

Some refugees disclosed that they had dodged the army and crossed to
Uganda through river Ishasha, which they said was a risk because the
volume of the water had increased due to the rains.

[Byline: Caleb Bahikaho]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

